race.comment: RED SPHERE (11) was a comfortable winner of his penultimate start, before finding the longer distance last start a touch beyond him at this stage of his career. He is nicely placed here with Liam Riordan in the saddle, and from a good draw, he is well-placed to bounce back. MAGNAPRIME (5) returns from a nine-month break, which would have done him the world of good. He has won his latest 2 tune-up trials and is sure to be right in the finish fresh up. SKIN IN THE GAME (9) had a terrific maiden prep, winning 3 times. The wide draw hurts him fresh up, but he is headed for better things and could be just too good for them. Check the market moves. NIGHT PEOPLE (3) is a handy gelding resuming from a spell. He has been a fresh-up winner in the past, and he cannot be taken lightly here. Check the market moves.
